// ===========================================================================
// MEZZA DATA BANK SCHEMA — v2 (post-reconciliation against epik_extracted.json)
// ===========================================================================
//
// This is the contract between the Python extraction script and the Data Bank UI.
//
// Every jsonPath in this file has been verified against the real extracted_json
// output. Every field key matches a key the script actually produces. The only
// exceptions are fields explicitly marked `manualFill: true`, which the script
// does NOT yet produce — these display in the UI with an empty state and
// require the analyst to fill them by hand using the override flow.
//
// FIELD ATTRIBUTES:
//   key         — exact JSON key under jsonPath in extracted_json
//   label       — display label for the analyst
//   type        — text | number | currency | percent | date | boolean
//   editable    — analyst can override via PATCH /cases/{id}/extracted-field
//   required    — counts toward the completeness badge
//   manualFill  — true if the script does NOT produce this field; analyst fills
//                 it manually via the override mechanism. Shows a different
//                 visual affordance ("Enter manually" hint).
//   mirroredFrom — read-only display of another section's value (no override)
//   note        — inline help text shown next to the field
//   policyRef   — citation to the underwriting policy section/rule
//
// SECTION ATTRIBUTES:
//   id          — URL slug and React key
//   label       — section name in the sub-nav
//   group       — "legal" | "financial" | "analysis"
//   jsonPath    — dotted path inside extracted_json (empty string = root)
//   fields      — ordered list of field objects (see above)
//   tableRender — true if this section's jsonPath points at an array and the
//                 page should render it as a table rather than a field list.
//                 If true, `fields` describes the columns of the table.
//   nested      — optional list of {label, jsonPath} for nested objects to
//                 render as sub-cards (used by cross_checks for affiliated
//                 parties, march_2025_closure, pos_system_mismatch)
//
// CHANGES VS v1:
//   + identity: renamed `group_name` → `operator_group`, `location` → 3 fields,
//     `concept` → `venue_type`. Added website, holding_entity, lettable_sqm,
//     venue_legal_name, location_district, specific_location, sub_industry.
//   + trade_licence: renamed `activities` → `permitted_activities`. Added
//     formation_number, company_name_en, company_name_ar, company_type,
//     days_to_expiry, years_operational, licence_period_years.
//   + moa: renamed `share_capital_aed` → `capital_aed`, `establishment_date`
//     → `execution_date`. Replaced `ownership_summary` with individuals and
//     corporate_shareholders (now rendered separately as tables in future).
//   + lease: kept the 4 real fields (annual_rent_aed, rent_as_pct_of_net_revenue,
//     source, note). Added 11 manualFill fields per policy 2.2 requirements
//     (Ejari, expiry, term, escalation, security deposit, rent-free).
//   + vat: collapsed two former sections (vat_certificate + vat_returns) into
//     one. Quarterly returns array is tableRender. Added stagger, signatory.
//   + pos_headline (new): the 19-field POS summary from script.
//   + pos_monthly: now points at the array, tableRender:true. 12 rows.
//   + pos_accounting_groups (renamed from pos_category_mix): tableRender:true.
//     22 rows. By drink/menu category from the POS system.
//   + cogs: rewrote to show 3-scenario blended (low/mid/high), chosen, GP.
//   + other_expenses: added 3-scenario totals and 6-row category table.
//   + pnl: rewrote to single P&L per Pranit's decision. Shows corrected
//     EBIT/salary only by default. Notes preserved.
//   + cross_checks: added 3 nested rich objects (affiliated_parties,
//     march_2025_closure, pos_system_mismatch).
//   + credit_score (new section, "Scoring Engine Output"): 29 fields plus
//     score_breakdown (10-row table) and outstanding_queries (6-row table).
//   + policy_checks (new section): computed at render time from reality
//     values vs policy thresholds. No jsonPath. Frontend derives it.
//
// FIELDS DROPPED FROM v1:
//   - identity.group_name (now operator_group)
//   - vat_returns section (merged into vat)
//   - vat_certificate section (merged into vat)
//   - seasonality section (data is in pos_monthly.seasonality_pct column)
//   - salary section (data is in pnl.salary_aed_corrected)
//   - pos_category_mix (renamed to pos_accounting_groups, restructured)
//
// ===========================================================================

